                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-170" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN EGAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I came from Norwich. I was with the prosecutor, and saw the prisoner lift his coat, take the handkerchief and give it another person—I turned and seized him by the collar and said, "Get me the handkerchief—he said, "I have not got it"—which I knew he had not.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. I was going down Holborn, this gentleman missed the handkerchief and turned and collared me, and said, "Give me the hand kerchief or I will prosecute you"—I said I had not got it, and he took me along—I called the watchman myself.</p>
